d at last, is more powerful than a net of rope.\n\n- Patricia A. McKillip, The Forgotten Beasts of Eld\n|\nWhen a man is no longer anxious to do better than well, he is done for.\n\n- Benjamin\n|\nWhen the pain of being the same becomes greater than the pain of being different, you change.\n\n- Deepak Chopra, Why Is God Laughing?: The Path to Joy and Spiritual Optimism\n|\nLead me, follow me, or get the hell out of my way.\n\n- George S. Patton Jr., Patton Principles\n|\nI like movies. Movies have afforded me a modicum of luxuries. The thing about the movies is, if you're bad in a movie, you're bad forever.\n\n- Anthony\n|\nTo have a solid foundation of skepticism, -that is to say, the faculty of changing at any moment, of turning back, of facing successively the metamorphoses of life.\n\n- Rémy de Gourmont, Philosophic Nights in Paris,: Being Selections from Promenades Philosophiques\n|\nWhen excellence comes in at the door, failure flies out the window.\n\n- Matshona\n|\nThe moment you make the internal changes necessary to obtain your goal, the outside world changes instantly.\n\n- Chris Prentiss, Be Who You Want, Have What You Want: Change Your Thinking, Change Your Life\n|\nI’m going,’ he said, and in the temple light, I caught his determination, and that strength he got from loving me. It made him brave.\n\n- Jodi Meadows, Asunder\n|\nLife is an experiment, experiment by sending as many ideas in the universe and see which idea takes off and put your heart into that.\n\n- Matthew\n|\nDuring Uthman's caliphate, a Muslim embassy was sent to China to establish diplomatic relations\n\n- Firas Alkhateeb, Lost Islamic History: Reclaiming Muslim Civilisation from the Past\n|\nMore love, more power.Less love, less power.Great love, great power.\n\n- Matshona\n|\nSadness wasn't a disease you could catch, as far as I know, but from what I seen, people treated it like it was.\n\n- L M Bryski, Book of Birds\n|\nClever man is a chicken; it can fly, but a little. Genius, on 